                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>New <sic>york</sic> 134 Elm St</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <date>Feby 16<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> 5608</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>Dear Sir/</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I have been so much engaged since<lb/> the rect of yours dated\n                        <date>9<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> Feby</date> that I could not find<lb/> time to\n                reply thereto <sic>untill</sic> this moment—The<lb/> commencement of your Letter\n                gave me much pain<lb/> as it was far, very far from my thoughts when I wrote<lb/> to\n                you concerning the B. H. B Society—to wound your<lb/> feelings in the slightest\n                degree—all that I wished<lb/> to know from you was whether the article that you<lb/>\n                inserted in your Periodical was an official one—and<lb/> whether the party who sent\n                it had omitted part of the<lb/> minutes ignorantly which would have been likely\n                enough<lb/> if it had been conveyed to you from a private source<lb/> Rest assured\n                my dear sir I have too high an opinion of<lb/> you to suppose for one moment that\n                you yourself (to use<lb/> your own words) would be guilty of such meanness as<lb/>\n                to insert only a part of the minutes—</p>\n            <p>I will as briefly as possible give you my reasons for asking<lb/> you for the\n                information—when the B. H. B. Society was<lb/> first instituted, a resolution was\n                passed (at least so I am<lb/> informed) electing all the <add>חזנים</add> in\n                    <placeName>New York</placeName> Honorary Members<lb/> and Letters were sent\n                accordingly informing us of such<lb/> resolution &amp;c &amp;c The one I received\n                was “word for word” the<lb/> same as yours—I felt that an honorary membership<lb/>\n                would not be of any value to a charitable Institution<lb/> and in my reply to their\n                Letter I told them so at the same<lb/> time requesting them to admit me as a pay\n                member. I received <del>another</del> a Letter in answer accepting me as a<lb/>\n                subscriber with sundry compliments &amp;c &amp;c—<lb/> Now my dear sir judge my\n                surprise on reading the<lb/> extract of the minutes in the “Occident”</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3c82513w/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
