              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3c82513w/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>and I ask you whether it is not an insult<lb/> to my Brother <add>חזנים</add> as well\n                as to myself<lb/> to see a partial statement of the minutes<lb/> published making it\n                appear (if officially sent)<lb/> that <persName>Mr Isaacs</persName> is the only\n                    <add>חזן</add> that <del>that</del> the<lb/> B. H. B. Society think worthy of\n                their notice—<lb/> for my own part I read it in this way that it<lb/> was another\n                link added to the chain of “quack<lb/> advertisements” that you had innocently\n                inserted<lb/> in your paper to land a particular person and<lb/> his patrons—or\n                maybe it was or is intended to be<lb/> the commencement of a new series—</p>\n            <p>It is supposed that either <persName>Mr Godfrey</persName> or <persName>Mr\n                    Isaacs</persName><lb/> or both together sent you the particulars—whoever<lb/>\n                the party may be they have incurred the censure<lb/> of the committee in consequence\n                at least so <del>one</del> I am<lb/> informed by one of the managers—</p>\n            <p>You will probably receive a new notice “from the Board<lb/> what it may be I know not\n                there is however only one<lb/> course open to them that will satisfy me—and\n                that<lb/> is to publish in your work. That the 1<hi rend=\"sup\">st</hi> article\n                sent<lb/> was without the sanction of their Board—that it<lb/> was a false statement\n                giving the reason why &amp;c</p>\n            <p>You entirely mistake me if you think I wish to<lb/> appear in print in this matter in\n                the shape of<lb/> puffery—I therefore do not comply with your<lb/> well meaning\n                request viz to send you my Letters<lb/> for insertion—In respect to the\n                “Occident”<lb/> a work of inestimable value in my eyes I would<lb/> I had the power\n                of increasing its circulation, but the<lb/> majority of my congregation are opposed\n                to it and were<lb/> so when I arrived in <placeName><sic>america</sic></placeName>\n                owing I believe to the</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3c82513w/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
